title: BEGINNER CALISTHENICS WORKOUT
description:
Let me know if you try this Push Pull Calisthenics workout, I’ve made it specifically for beginners, so DON’T STRESS. 

There are progression exercises for each calisthenics exercise, so you can work your way up in intensity depending on your level

I’m committed to helping you feel your best and MOST capable self in your body, and this workout was made to train the FOUNDATIONAL STRENGTH you need, which will benefit your lifting too 

Let me know, what else you want to see & I LOVE YOU

Quick notes!

BLOODFLOW
(jumping, jogging, skipping) - 2 mins
MOBILITY
- Wrist flexor & extensor stretches (1-2mins)
- wrist rotation - 10-15 secs each
- arm rotation, shoulder dislocations, shoulder rolls - each warmup 10-15 secs
THE WORKOUT
- Pushups (3 sets × 8-10 reps) "retracting & protracting"
OR
Negative pushups (3 sets × 5-8 reps) OR incline
- Pull ups (if u can, 3 sets × 5-10 reps)
OR. 4 progression:
Dead hang (5-10 secs)
Scapula bar pulls (5-10 re reps)
Chin to bar hold (3 sets - 5-10 secs)
Negative pull-ups (3 sets, 5 reps)
Scapula should be engaged well

- Tricep dips 🪑 (3 sets × 8 reps)
OR
Tricep negative (3 sets, 5-8 reps)
